title: For Sale:  Benelli M4, M3, Remington 1100...
postcontent: Quick and dirty sale listing for a few guns I'm going to divest. If there's no interest I'll post more thourough individual listings with pictures this weekend, but prices will be higher by then. I'm feeling lazy right now, so if you bite, you'll win. First, Remington 1100 with 2x barrels. Gun is flawless mechanically, but probably 85-90% cosmetically. one barrel is 18" smooth bore with rifle sights, one barrel is 26" vent rib with bead sight. $450 gets the package. Second, Benelli M3 super 90. Gun is used, in 90% costmetic condition. Mechanically it runs well, but seems a bit ammo finicky, which is why I'm selling it. I've installed a tube extension so it's 7+1+1, and it has the factory pistol grip fixed stock on it. Ghost ring sights, but buyer will have to source screws for and install rear sight (which I'll include) as the place I got it from had taken off the rear sight to mount a god awful B square bridge mount and they didn't have the rear sight to give me. I spent $115 to get a new rear sight, but purchased the wrong screws to instal it and haven't followed up on it since. My loss, your gain. $1100. (note, if you don't know what an M3 is, look it up... it's badass... one of the only pump/semi shotguns out there). Third, Benelli M4. this one does not have the full length tube, but does have the collapsible stock that was for the longest time impossible to get outside LE channels. This particular M4 has a very nice, very expensive but currently out of production full length quad rail on it. the gun is in about 85-90% condition cosmetically, and runs great as long as you're using full power loads in it. $1750. I'm only selling to fund some other projects, so I'm not super motivated to move the stuff, so please no lowball offers. I will, however, reward people for not wasting my time, and will give discounts for package sales.
